0discovering%20more%20about%20life%20in%20space%2C%20and%20they%20keep%20meticulous%20track%20of%20how%20their%20bodies%20respond%20to%20the%20weightless%20environment.%20Some%20of%20what%20they've%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Fmissions%2Fstation%2F15-ways-the-international-space-station-benefits-humanity-back-on-earth%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elearned%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20led%20to%20developments%20in%20drugs%20and%20medical%20technology%20that%20benefit%20humans%20on%20Earth%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThere's%20not%20a%20lot%20of%20room%20on%20the%20ISS.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221266%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20astronaut%20with%20short%20hair%20holds%20a%20book%20under%20her%20arm%20in%20a%20small%20cubby%20on%20the%20ISS%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67f6ca26a466d2b74ab2b6dd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22875%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAstronaut%20Peggy%20Whitson%20in%20the%20doorway%20of%20the%20Temporary%20Sleep%20Station%20(TSS)%20on%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20in%202002.%3Cp%3ENASA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20more%20like%20a%20not-a-lot-of-space%20station.%20It's%20a%20six-bedroom%20house%20packed%20into%20an%20area%20that's%20shorter%20than%20a%20football%20field%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Finternational-space-station%2Fspace-station-facts-and-figures%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENASA%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Five%20agencies%20share%20the%20station%2C%20which%20has%20six%20sleeping%20quarters%2C%20a%20gym%2C%20and%20two%20bathrooms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAstronaut%20Frank%20Rubio%20described%20it%20as%20a%20building%20made%20of%20hallways%2C%20with%20no%20large%20space%20like%20a%20living%20room%20to%20gather.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20almost%20have%20to%20block%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20is%20so%20small%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Fpodcasts%2Fhouston-we-have-a-podcast%2Fsurpassing-a-year-in-space%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHouston%3A%20We%20Have%20a%20Podcast%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20food%20isn't%20all%20freeze-dried.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221859%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20in%20a%20blue%20shirt%20holds%20a%20spoon%20and%20food%20container%20on%20the%20ISS%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67f6d750c6ad288d147db84f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221265%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAstronaut%20Leroy%20Chiao%20eats%20a%20meal%20on%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20in%202005.%3Cp%3ENASA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fastronaut-leland-melvin-space-food-taste-good-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESpace%20food%3C%2Fa%3E%20needs%20to%20meet%20a%20few%20requirements.%20It%20can't%20crumble%20to%20bits%20and%20clog%20up%20machinery%2C%20it%20has%20to%20be%20able%20to%20stay%20fresh%20for%20months%2C%20and%20it%20should%20taste%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20newer%20methods%20for%20preserving%20food%20for%20long-distance%20travel%20have%20given%20astronauts%20more%20meal%20options%2C%20and%20ISS%20astronauts%20can%20make%20everything%20from%20spicy%20shrimp%20to%20chocolate%20pudding%20cake.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20it%20was%20really%20tasty%2C%26quot%3B%20retired%20astronaut%20Leland%20Melvin%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELots%20of%20astronauts%20like%20spicier%20options%20because%20the%20lack%20of%20gravity%20makes%20fluid%20float%20into%20their%20sinuses%2C%20making%20them%20stuffed%20up%20and%20affecting%20how%20food%20tastes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAstronauts%20and%20cosmonauts%20will%20often%20bring%20snacks%20that%20remind%20them%20of%20home.%20For%20example%2C%20one%20of%20Rubio's%20crewmates%20brought%20items%20for%20a%20charcuterie%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EDaily%20exercise%20helps%20prevent%20bone%20loss.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222842%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20in%20sneakers%20uses%20a%20large%20workout%20machine%20with%20one%20leg%20raised%20on%20the%20ISS%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67f6d6cfa466d2b74ab2ba56%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223087%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAstronaut%20Sandra%20Magnus%20exercises%20on%20the%20advanced%20Resistive%20Exercise%20Device%20(aRED)%20on%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20in%202009.%3Cp%3ENASA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20on%20in%20space%20travel%2C%20doctors%20realized%20astronauts%20were%20losing%20bone%20density%20after%20spending%20long%20periods%20of%20time%20in%20a%20weightless%20environment.%20Now%2C%20ISS%20residents%20do%20a%20couple%20of%20hours%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-nasa-astronaut-peggy-whitson-builds-strength-2018-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexercise%20every%20day%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20help%20prevent%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20mix%20of%20cardio%20and%20load-bearing%20workouts%2C%20Rubio%20said.%20They%20do%20so%20many%20squats%20that%20%26quot%3Bevery%20day%20is%20leg%20day%20in%20space%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThere's%20a%20technique%20for%20brushing%20your%20teeth%20without%20running%20water.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20with%20a%20mustache%20and%20wearing%20a%20blue-and-white-striped%20shirt%20holds%20a%20silver%20packet%20with%20a%20straw%20on%20the%20ISS%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67f6d610c6ad288d147db7f3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221312%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAstronaut%20Scott%20Altman%20holds%20a%20drink%20container%20on%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20in%202000.%3Cp%3ENASA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202013%2C%20retired%20astronaut%20Chris%20Hadfield%20demonstrated%20how%20he%20brushed%20his%20teeth%20in%20space%20on%20the%20Canadian%20Space%20Agency's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D3bCoGC532p8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EYouTube%3C%2Fa%3E%20channel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20he%20used%20a%20resealable%20water%20container%20to%20wet%20the%20toothbrush.%20Then%20he%20slurped%20the%20water%20off%20the%20brush%20and%20applied%20regular%20toothpaste.%20When%20he%20was%20done%2C%20he%20swallowed%20the%20toothpaste%20and%20filled%20his%20mouth%20with%20water%20to%20clean%20the%20toothbrush.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShowers%20are%20actually%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-astronauts-cant-do-in-space-2019-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esponge%20baths%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20washcloths%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2015%2F05%2F167746main_fs_livingandworkinginspace508c.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENASA%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Astronauts%20use%20shampoo%20that%20they%20don't%20have%20to%20rinse%20out.%20Suction%20takes%20care%20of%20extra%20water%2C%20which%20then%20goes%20to%20a%20waste%20tank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20toilets%20on%20the%20ISS%20rely%20on%20airflow.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224754%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20hand%20holds%20a%20hose%20attached%20to%20a%20space%20toilet%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5f6a4d5f49479600287bd962%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223536%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20team%20member%20at%20Johnson%20Space%20Flight%20Center%20lifts%20the%20urine%20hose%20of%20a%20space%20toilet.%3Cp%3ENASA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHoses%2C%20funnels%2C%20and%20suction%20are%20all%20crucial%20components%20when%20it's%20time%20to%20go%20in%20space.%20In%202020%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftoilet-n