3EAstronauts%20Scott%20Kelly%20and%20Kjell%20Lindgren%20eat%20space%20plants%20on%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20in%202015.%3Cp%3ENASA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20humans%20are%20going%20to%20live%20on%20Mars%2C%20they%20must%20first%20perfect%20space%20gardening.%20Fresh%20produce%20is%20key%20to%20providing%20necessary%20nutrients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Vegetable%20Production%20System%2C%20or%20Veggie%2C%20is%20the%20space%20station's%20six-plant%20garden%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Fexploration-research-and-technology%2Fgrowing-plants-in-space%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENASA%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It's%20helping%20astronauts%20learn%20how%20to%20make%20food%20without%20gravity%20and%20sunlight.%20They've%20grown%20peppers%20and%20lettuce%20on%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ENASA%20keeps%20a%20close%20eye%20on%20astronauts'%20health%20before%2C%20during%2C%20and%20after%20their%20time%20on%20ISS.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20holds%20a%20medical%20device%20to%20her%20eye%20on%20the%20ISS%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67f6c6ba3fe8d39283629d1d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAstronaut%20Serena%20Au%C3%B1%C3%B3n-Chancellor%20uses%20a%20Fundoscope%20to%20examine%20her%20eye%20on%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20in%202018.%3Cp%3ENASA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELong%20spaceflights%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-happens-effects-human-body-space%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echange%20astronauts'%20bodies%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20lot%20of%20ways.%20The%20lack%20of%20gravity%20affects%20their%20balance%20and%20ability%20to%20walk.%20The%20brain%20adapts%20to%20the%20lack%20of%20gravity%2C%20and%20some%20of%20these%20changes%20can%20become%20permanent%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.ufl.edu%2F2025%2F03%2Fwilmore-williams-astronaut-health-effects%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUniversity%20of%20Florida%3C%2Fa%3E%20researchers%20recently%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAstronauts%20routinely%20track%20their%20own%20health%2C%20taking%20saliva%20samples%20and%20wearing%20monitors%20for%20heart%20rate%2C%20sleep%2C%20and%20temperature.%20Not%20only%20will%20such%20data%20be%20helpful%20for%20future%20missions%2C%20but%20some%20research%20could%20affect%20people%20on%20Earth%2C%20too%2C%20especially%20those%20who%20live%20in%20remote%20areas%20with%20less%20access%20to%20medical%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EHaircuts%20aboard%20the%20ISS%20are%20doable.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20cuts%20a%20woman's%20hair%20while%20she%20holds%20a%20vacuum%20hose%20near%20her%20neck%20on%20the%20ISS%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67f6c51dc6ad288d147db37d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221277%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAstronaut%20Terry%20Virts%20cuts%20ESA%20astronaut%20Samantha%20Cristoforetti's%20hair%20on%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20in%202015.%3Cp%3ENASA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESix%20months%20can%20be%20a%20long%20time%20to%20go%20without%20a%20haircut.%20Astronauts%20can%20get%20a%20trim%2C%20provided%20they%20have%20a%20vacuum%20on%20hand%20to%20capture%20the%20clippings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EIt%20can%20be%20tough%20to%20sleep%20through%2016%20sunrises%20a%20day.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221919%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20people%20zipped%20into%20gray%20sleeping%20bags%20wearing%20sleep%20masks%20on%20the%20ISS%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67f6c477c6ad288d147db353%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221275%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAstronauts%20Thomas%20D.%20Jones%20and%20Mark%20L.%20Polansky%20in%20sleeping%20bags%20on%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20in%202001.%3Cp%3ENASA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20ISS%20orbits%20the%20Earth%2C%20it%20experiences%20the%20sun%20rising%20and%20setting%2016%20times%20a%20day.%20That's%20just%20one%20reason%20astronauts%20may%20have%20trouble%20catching%20their%20z's.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERubio%20described%20crew%20quarters%20as%20a%20phone%20booth.%20Inside%2C%20there's%20a%20sleeping%20bag%20attached%20to%20the%20wall%20to%20keep%20sleeping%20astronauts%20from%20floating%20and%20knocking%20into%20walls.%20He%20actually%20enjoyed%20the%20weightless%20sleep%2C%20but%20for%20some%20people%2C%20it%20takes%20some%20getting%20used%20to%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ESome%20days%2C%20it's%20nice%20to%20step%20outside%20for%20a%20spacewalk.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20astronaut%20in%20a%20spacesuit%20above%20the%20Earth%2C%20holding%20onto%20the%20ISS%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67f6c2d73fe8d39283629c38%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221261%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAstronaut%20Donald%20Pettit%20on%20a%20spacewalk%20at%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20in%202003.%3Cp%3ENASA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20ISS%20needs%20maintenance%20or%20repairs%2C%20astronauts%20get%20suited%20up%20for%20a%20spacewalk.%20There%20have%20been%20over%20270%20since%201998%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Finternational-space-station%2Fspace-station-spacewalks%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENASA%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Some%20have%20been%20only%20a%20couple%20of%20hours%2C%20others%20have%20taken%20over%20eight%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20suits%20are%20equipped%20with%20oxygen%20and%20water.%20Before%20heading%20out%20into%20space%2C%20astronauts%20breathe%20pure%20oxygen%20to%20rid%20their%20bodies%20of%20nitrogen%20and%20avoid%20getting%20%26quot%3Bthe%20bends%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20is%20a%20condition%20often%20associated%20with%20scuba%20diving.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAstronauts%20actually%20do%20a%20lot%20of%20training%20underwater%20on%20Earth%20before%20doing%20a%20real%20spacewalk.%20Nothing%20can%20quite%20prepare%20them%20for%20the%20real%20thing%2C%20though%2C%20astronaut%20Nick%20Hague%20told%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Fpodcasts%2Fhouston-we-have-a-podcast%2Fcrew-9%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHouston%3A%20We%20Have%20a%20Podcast%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20just%20can't%20replicate%20that%20floating%20around%20in%20a%20spacesuit%20in%20the%20vacuum%20of%20space%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20only%20place%20you%20do%20it%20real%20for%20the%20first%20time%20is%20in%20space.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20view%20from%20inside%20isn't%20bad%2C%20either.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20cloudy%20Earth%20seen%20from%20a%20window%20on%20the%20ISS%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67f6c211a466d2b74ab2b4f4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221277%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Earth%20seen%20from%20the%20International%20Space%20Station's%20Cupola%20window%20in%202015.%3Cp%3ENASA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20major%20perks%20of%20spending%20time%20on%20the%20ISS%20is%20its%20view%20of%20the%20Earth.%20Astronauts%20have%20seen%20hurricanes%2C%20lightning%2C%20and%20glittering%20cities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fastronauts-best-photos-from-space-station-this-year-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincredible%20photos%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20prove%20it.%20Some%20astronauts%2C%20including%20Don%20Pettit%2C%20are%20known%20for%20their%20astrophotography.%20He%20brought%20a%20lot%20of%20equipment%20on%20board%20to%20help%20himself%20and%20his%20fellow%20crew%20members%20take%20even%20better%20pictures%2C%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%2