ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdelhi-air-pollution-cag-report-arvind-kejriwal-you-let-1-lakh-vehicles-pollute-bjp-targets-arvind-kejriwal-over-report-8061884%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EArvind%20Kejriwal-led%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%3C%2Fa%3E%20(AAP)%2C%C2%A0then%20issued%20instructions%20to%20provide%20proper%20shelter%20for%20the%20stray%20cattle%20in%20the%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20allocation%20of%20Rs%2040%20crore%20has%20also%20been%20made%20for%20setting%20up%20a%20'Model%20Gaushala'%20(modern%20cow%20shelter)%20in%20Delhi's%20annual%20budget.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1744446060000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-04%2Fks0paao8_rekha-gupta-cow-video_625x300_12_April_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fdelhi-news%2Fdelhi-chief-minister-rekha-gupta-sees-man-feeding-roti-to-cow-on-busy-road-does-this-8146922%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ms%20Gupta%20posted%20the%20video%20of%20her%20interaction%20with%20the%20man%20on%20X%20and%20requested%20Delhiites%20not%20to%20throw%20'roti'%20or%20any%20food%20on%20the%20road.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Supreme%20Court%20Sets%203-Month%20Deadline%20For%20President%20To%20Decide%20On%20Bills%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20first%20time%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20prescribed%20that%20the%20president%20should%20decide%20on%20the%20bills%20reserved%20for%20her%20consideration%20by%20the%20governor%20within%20a%20period%20of%20three%20months%20from%20the%20date%20on%20which%20such%20reference%20is%20received.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFour%20days%20after%20the%20top%20court%20cleared%2010%20bills%2C%20which%20were%20stalled%20and%20reserved%20by%20Tamil%20Nadu%20Governor%20R%20N%20Ravi%20for%20the%20president's%20consideration%2C%20and%20set%20a%20timeline%20for%20all%20governors%20to%20act%20on%20the%20bills%20passed%20by%20the%20state%20assemblies%2C%20the%20judgement%20running%20into%20415%20pages%20was%20uploaded%20on%20the%20top%20court's%20website%20at%2010.54%20pm%20on%20Friday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20deem%20it%20appropriate%20to%20adopt%20the%20timeline%20prescribed%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs...%20and%20prescribe%20that%20the%20President%20is%20required%20to%20take%20a%20decision%20on%20the%20bills%20reserved%20for%20his%20consideration%20by%20the%20Governor%20within%20a%20period%20of%20three%20months%20from%20the%20date%20on%20which%20such%20reference%20is%20received.%20In%20case%20of%20any%20delay%20beyond%20this%20period%2C%20appropriate%20reasons%20would%20have%20to%20be%20recorded%20and%20conveyed%20to%20the%20concerned%20State.%20The%20States%20are%20also%20required%20to%20be%20collaborative%20and%20extend%20co-operation%20by%20furnishing%20answers%20to%20the%20queries%20which%20may%20be%20raised%20and%20consider%20the%20suggestions%20made%20by%20the%20Central%20government%20expeditiously%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20top%20court%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20bench%20of%20Justices%20JB%20Pardiwala%20and%20R%20Mahadevan%20on%20April%208%20set%20aside%20the%20reservation%20of%20the%2010%20bills%20for%20the%20president's%20consideration%20in%20the%20second%20round%20holding%20it%20as%20illegal%2C%20erroneous%20in%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithout%20mincing%20words%2C%20the%20court%20said%20%26quot%3Bwhere%20the%20Governor%20reserves%20a%20Bill%20for%20the%20consideration%20of%20the%20President%20and%20the%20President%20in%20turn%20withholds%20assent%20thereto%20then%2C%20it%20shall%20be%20open%20to%20the%20State%20Government%20to%20assail%20such%20an%20action%20before%20this%20Court%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArticle%20200%20of%20the%20Constitution%20empowers%20the%20governor%20to%20give%20assent%20to%20the%20bills%20presented%20to%20him%2C%20withhold%20the%20assent%20or%20to%20reserve%20it%20for%20the%20consideration%20of%20the%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Bills%2C%20having%20been%20pending%20with%20the%20Governor%20for%20an%20unduly%20long%20period%20of%20time%2C%20and%20the%20Governor%20having%20acted%20with%20clear%20lack%20of%20bona%20fides%20in%20reserving%20the%20Bills%20for%20the%20consideration%20of%20the%20President%2C%20immediately%20after%20the%20pronouncement%20of%20the%20decision%20of%20this%20Court%20in%20State%20of%20Punjab%20(supra)%2C%20are%20deemed%20to%20have%20been%20assented%20to%20by%20the%20Governor%20on%20the%20date%20when%20they%20were%20presented%20to%20him%20after%20being%20reconsidered.%20There%20is%20no%20expressly%20specified%20time-limit%20for%20the%20discharge%20of%20the%20functions%20by%20the%20Governor%20under%20Article%20200%20of%20the%20Constitution.%20Despite%20there%20being%20no%20prescribed%20time-limit%2C%20Article%20200%20cannot%20be%20read%20in%20a%20manner%20which%20allows%20the%20Governor%20to%20not%20take%20action%20upon%20bills%20which%20are%20presented%20to%20him%20for%20assent%20and%20thereby%20delay%20and%20essentially%20roadblock%20the%20law-making%20machinery%20in%20the%20State%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20said%20in%20its%20judgement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EObserving%20that%20the%20governor%20is%20required%20to%20abide%20by%20the%20aid%20and%20advice%20tendered%20by%20the%20Council%20of%20Ministers%2C%20the%20top%20court%20said%20it%20is%20not%20open%20for%20the%20governor%20to%20reserve%20a%20bill%20for%20the%20consideration%20of%20the%20President%20once%20it%20is%20presented%20to%20him%20in%20the%20second%20round%2C%20after%20having%20been%20returned%20to%20the%20House%20previously.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20expressly%20specified%20time-limit%20for%20the%20discharge%20of%20the%20functions%20by%20the%20Governor%20under%20Article%20200%20of%20the%20Constitution.%20Despite%20there%20being%20no%20prescribed%20time-limit%2C%20Article%20200%20cannot%20be%20read%20in%20a%20manner%20which%20allows%20the%20Governor%20to%20not%20take%20action%20upon%20bills%20which%20are%20presented%20to%20him%20for%20assent%20and%20thereby%20delay%20and%20essentially%20roadblock%20the%20law-making%20machinery%20in%20the%20State%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20said%20while%20directing%20the%20registry%20to%20send%20a%20copy%20each%20of%20this%20judgment%20to%20all%20the%20high%20courts%20and%20the%20principal%20secretaries%20to%20the%20governors%20of%20all%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20court%20set%20timelines%20and%20said%20failure%20to%20comply%20with%20it%20would%20make%20the%20inaction%20of%20the%20governors%20subject%20to%20judicial%20review%20by%20the%20courts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20case%20of%20either%20withholding%20of%20assent%20or%20reservation%20of%20the%20bill%20for%20the%20consideration%20of%20the%20President%2C%20upon%20the%20aid%20and%20advice%20of%20the%20State%20Council%20of%20Ministers%2C%20the%20Governor%20is%20expected%20to%20take%20such%20an%20action%20forthwith%2C%20subject%20to%20a%20maximum%20period%20of%20one-month%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20court%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20case%20of%20withholding%20of%20assent%20contrary%20to%20the%20advice%20of%20the%20State%20Council%20of%20Ministers%2C%20the%20Governor%20must%20return%20the%20bill%20together%20with%20a%20message%20within%20a%20maximum%20period%20of%20three%20months.%20In%20case%20of%20reservation%20of%20bills%20for%20the%20consideration%20of%20the%20President%20contrary%20to%20the%20advice%20of%20the%20State%20Council%20of%20Ministers%2C%20the%20Governor%20shall%20make%20such%20reservation%20within%20a%20maximum%20period%20of%20three%20months%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20case%20of%20presentation%20of%20a%20bill%20after%20reconsideration%2C%20the%20governor%20must%20grant%20assent%20forthwith%2C%20subject%20to%20a%20maximum%20period%20of%20one-month%2C%20the%20court%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20said%20that%20the%20governor%20couldn't%20sit%20over%20bills%20and%20adopt%20the%20concept%20of%20%26quot%3Babsolute%20veto%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bpocket%20veto%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20'pocket%20veto'%20or%20'absolute%20veto'%20available%20to%20the%20President%20in%20discharge%20of%20his%20functions%20under%20Article%20201.%20The%20use%20of%20the%20expression%20%26quot%3Bshall%20declare%26quot%3B%20makes%20it%20mandatory%20for%20the%20President%20to%20make%20a%20choice%20between%20the%20two%20options%20available%20under%20the%20substantive%20part%20of%20Article%20201%2C%20that%20is%2C%20to%20either%20grant%20assent%20or%20to%20withhold%20assent%20to%20a%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20constitutional%20scheme%20does%20not%2C%20in%20any%20manner%2C%20provide%20that%20a%20constitutional%20authority%20can%20exercise%20its%20powers%20under%20the%20Constitution%20arbitrarily%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20court%20exercised%20its%20plenary%20power%20under%20Article%20142%20of%20the%20Constitution%20to%20make%20the%20bill%20re-presented%20to%20the%20Tamil%20Nadu%20governor%2C%20as%20deemed%20to%20have%20been%20passed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20court%20had%20previously%20framed%20questions%20to%20answer%20in%20a%20dispute%20between%20Tamil%20Nadu%20government%20and%20the%20governor%20over%20the%20delay%20in%20assent%20to%20bills%20passed%20by%20the%20legislative%20assembly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20delay%20in%20giving%20assent%20by%20the%20governor%20prompted%20the%20state%20government%20to%20move%20the%20top%20court%20in%202023%2C%20claiming%2012%20bills%2C%20including%20one%20from%202020%2C%20were%20pending%20with%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20November%2013%2C%202023%2C%20the%20governor%20declared%20he%20was%20withholding%20assent%20to%2010%20bills%20following%20which%20the%20legislative%20assembly%20convened%20a%20special%20session%20and%20re-enacted%20the%20very%20same%20bills%20on%20November%2018%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELater%2C%20som